Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In the past 24 hours, the USA (182 955), Brazil (45 449), and India (44 699) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 12 113 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (24-25 Nov 2020).

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (12 countries) include the USA, Brazil, India, Italy (25852), Russia (23 675), Germany (20 825), UK (18 213), France (16 282), Poland (15 356), Ukraine (13 882), Iran (13 843), and Mexico (10 335). A total of 61 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 33 of the 61 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 10 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 5 are from the South East Asia region, 2 are from the Western Pacific region, and 2 are from the African region.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 13%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 10.8%.

Impression: The global daily reported cases continue to increase with over 600 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours. Countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean and the South East Asia regions. The USA continues to show uncontrolled transmission. - Mod.UBA]
